abstract.value: This vocabulary defines the terms used to express ACLs in WoN, as well as SHACL shapes for validating such ACLs.

comment.en: Class of the roots of ASE trees
Half-open state. The connection has been opened by the remote counterpart but not yet been accepted by the local end.
Suggested state. The Connection has been created through a Hint Event but not yet been opened by either of the sides.
The connected state. Messages are forwarded to/from the owner.
The closed state. No Messages are forwarded in this state. Re-opening a connection is possbile.
Half-open state. The Connection has been requested by the local end but not yet been accepted by the remote counterpart.
A Connection's state.
Class of all WoN operations, such as reading the linked data representation of a resource, sending a message, etc.
Placeholder for the atom's own URI in an atom expression, e.g. `[ auth:atom auth:self ]`.
Placeholder for any atom URI in an atom expression, e.g. `[ auth:atom auth:anyAtom ]`

Placeholder for the URI of the socket that requests an operation via auth:localAuth, or
     of the local socket of the connection of which the target socket requests an operation via auth:targetAuth.

Placeholder for the uri of the atom or node that requests an operation. In the case of bearer
    authentication, there is no operationRequestor; arguably, one could use the token's subject claim, but that
    would extend additional trust to the issuer of the token.
An expression evaluating to an atom URI relative to a given evaluation context.
Implicit authorization for established connections
Implicit authorization for closed connections
Implicit authorization granting any operation to bearers of a valid token with scope auth:OwnerToken
Implicit authorization for connections that have been requested by us but have not yet been accepted by the partner
Implicit authorization for connections that have been requested by the partner but not yet established

Implicit authorization granting the WoN node hosting an atom that we we have a connection
    with access to our key graph so the node can verify messages we send.
Implicit authorization granting an token with scope auth:OwnerToken to the atom's owner

Class of authorizations in WoN. Authorizations combine definitions of __who__ is allowed __what__ and if they are not, under which circumstances they may learn how to obtain access (i.e., get __authInfo__).
Class of all ASE that correspond to the connection position in the atom tree structure.
Class of all ASE that correspond to the graph position in the atom tree structure.
Specification of URI prefixes for atoms, events, and connections for a WoN node.

comment.undefined:
An LDP container with all the Atoms stored on the Node.

The container supports LDP paging as described here: https://github.com/researchstudio-sat/webofneeds/blob/master/webofneeds/won-node-webapp/doc/linked-data-paging.md

comment.en: Class of all authentication tokens (when expressed in RDF, which makes sense for testing).
Class of all ASE that correspond to the connection container position in the atom tree structure.

URI reserved for the value of the scope claim of shared context tokens. Such tokens are
    used to prove that an atom has access to some (randomly defined) context and should be granted operations based on that.
    For example, an atom representing an organization could issue a shared context token to its members. In this case, the
    membership in the organization is the context they share. A socket that the organization supports might grant access to clients
    bearing a shared context token issued by the organization.
URI reserved for the value of the scope claim of owner tokens

comment.undefined: Class of all well-known token scopes. Using such scopes allows coordination across different domain ontologies.

comment.en: Graph type identifying the key graph of an atom (contains the public key)
Graph type identifying all content graphs of an atom (contains user-generated information)
Graph type identifying all acl graphs of an atom (contains the ACLs, there is one `#acl` and one `#socket-acl` graph).
Graph type identifying the sysinfo graph of an atom (contains system-generated information)
An expression evaluating to an atom URI, either relative to some evaluation context or by its absolute URI.
Class of all ASE that correspond to the socket position in the atom tree structure.
Class of all auth:OperationExpression instances that refer to requesting an authentication token.
Represents a Connection to between two Atoms. Whenever two Atoms are connected, each Atom creates a dedicated Connection object which encapsulate all information about the connection.
Class of all SHACL shapes that specify atom structure expressions (ASEs).
Class of all auth:TreeExpressionShape instances thay may contain a target atom expression via auth:targetAtom.

An atom is an online entity controlled by a person or organization. Its purpose is to be connected to other such atoms via Connections, so it can be said that it represents the need to interact with others.
It specifies a content - what the atom is about, which may be something that is offered for sale, sought for rental etc.
Class of all ASE that correspond to the atom message container position in the atom tree structure.
The deleted state. A deleted atom's URI is still remembered and associated with this state so that the WoN node can respond appropriately (410 GONE) when queried.
The incative state. Atoms do not communicate in this state. Intended to stop receiving messages for something not currently of interest.
The active state.
The Atom's state.
An Atom defines how Connections can be established using any number of Socket individuals. Each connection between two Atoms must specify the Socket it is attached to on each side.
Special wildcard matching any client - no credentials necessary. Example: `[ auth:grantee auth:anyone ; ... ]`
Expresses that any client is a grantee.
Message types for establishing and closing a connection
Hint message types
Messages used in established connections
Message types that modify an atom
Class of sets of msg:MessageType, identified by a resource, and listing message types via rdfs:member.
The operation of modifying an atom on behalf of that atom, i.e., the message is not signed using the atom owner's key
The operations of establishing or closing a connection or communicating via the connection on behalf of an atom, i.e., not signed by the atom owner's key
The operations of establishing or closing a connection on behalf of an atom, i.e., not signed by the atom owner's key
The operation of communicating with an atom via a connection, i.e, sending such messages __to__ the atom
The operation of establishing or closing a connection with another atom, i.e., sending such messages __to__ the atom
The operation of sending a hint message to an atom
The operations of communicating via a connection on behalf of an atom, i.e., not signed by the atom owner's key
Class of all auth:OperationExpression instances that refer to sending messages.
A server storing Atoms and the data associated with them.
Class of all ASE that correspond to the connection message position in the atom tree structure.
Superclass for Web of Needs protocol implementations.
Any message type
Expresses that any message type is covered by an operation.
Identifies the root of the atom's tree structure
Identifies the position of the __connection__ in the atom's tree structure
Identifies the position of the __socket__ in the atom's tree structure
Identifies the position of the __atom message__ in the atom's tree structure
Identifies the position of the __atom graph__ in the atom's tree structure
Identifies the position of the __atom message container__ in the atom's tree structure
Identifies the position of the __connection container__ in the atom's tree structure
Identifies the position of __connection message container__ in the atom's tree structure
Identifies the position of the __connection message__ in the atom's tree structure
Class of all positions in the atom's tree structure
Class of expected authorization evaluation results, specifying a) the decision, b) granted auth tokens (if any), c) authInfo (if any).
Class of all authorization evaluation results, specifying a) the decision, b) granted auth tokens (if any), c) authInfo (if any).

The 'operation' of observing an atom, i.e. being informed of changes to its content or connections.
        One could call this an inverse operation, being executed by the observed atom only for
        atoms that are granted the operation
Any operation at all
No operation - used where an operation is syntactically required but none should be allowed.

The 'operation' of auto-connecting an atom, i.e. automatically replying with a msg:ConnectMessage
    when a connection is requested. One could call this an inverse operation, being executed by the observed atom only for
        atoms that are granted the operation
The operation of reading a linked data resource
Class of all auth:OperationExpression instances that require no further defining properties beyond their identifier.
A Socket's definition.
Container for Messages. The container supports LDP paging as described here: https://github.com/researchstudio-sat/webofneeds/blob/master/webofneeds/won-node-webapp/doc/linked-data-paging.md.
The requested operation is denied.
The requested operation is granted.
The class of autorization decisions (access denied or granted)
Class of all definitions of token shapes, i.e. of specifications of the properties a token must have in order to be accepted.
Class of all auth:TreeExpressionShape instances thay may link to auth:OperationExpression instances via auth:operation.
Object properties that can be used to filter the focus nodes of ASE expressions.
Container for Connections. The container supports LDP paging as described here: https://github.com/researchstudio-sat/webofneeds/blob/master/webofneeds/won-node-webapp/doc/linked-data-paging.md
Class of all definition of tokens to be granted or tokens requested.
Class of all ASE that correspond to the connection message container position in the atom tree structure.
The Web of Needs protocol implementation that uses ActiveMQ.
Class of all auth:TreeExpressionShape instances that inherit allowed operations from their parent and are thus allowed to use the auth:inherit property to block inheritance.
Class of all ASE that correspond to the atom message position in the atom tree structure.
Class of all atom structure expressions (ASEs).
Specifies the lifetime of a token in seconds.
The date/time the token was issued, according to the signer's clock.
Defines a property to be 'derived' when the connection is established. The property will be used to derive a triple '[targetAtom] [property] [sourceAtom]'.
Filters focus nodes of the connection or connections expression by connection state.
Connects an WoN Node object with a description of a WON protocol it supports.
Defines the maximum number of established connections supported by the socket.
Authorization that a socket requests its own atom to add to its `#socket-acl` graph when it is added to the atom.
The issuer of an actual token (either an atom uri or a won node uri).
The number of connections in the container that are in state REQUEST_RECEIVED.
Identifies target atoms of connections that are direct or transitive targetNodes of the expression's focus nodes.

Allows an [auth:MessageOperationExpression] to specify [msg:MessageTypes] that the grantee of the operation may
     send __on behalf__ of the actual atom owner, at the operation's position in the atom's tree structure. The message
     types are either listed as objects of auth:messageOnBealf or defined
     transitively. In the latter case, the object of [auth:messageOnBehalf] is an [auth:MessageTypeSet], which in turn lists
     message types.
The token issued as the result of an ACL evaluation.
Indicates that any incoming CONNECT/OPEN message will be answered with OPEN unless the facet configuration forbids it.
Indicates that an atom or connection supports the specified socket (=behavior).

An authorization defines the operations it grants in the form of an ASE tree annotated with
        auth:OperationExpressions using auth:grant.
Filters focus nodes of the ASE root by atom state.
Filters focus nodes of the connection expression by connection IRI.
Links the Atom object to its connections.
Used in the ASE root to specify a auth:GraphExpression.
Filters focus nodes of the socket expression by socket definition IRI (not to be confused with auth:socketIri, which filters by IRI of the socket).
Identifies target WoN nodes of connections that are direct or transitive targetNodes of the expression's focus nodes.
The URI of the activeMQ broker

Atom structure expressions use `auth:inherit true` in order to not inherit granted operations from
        their parent expressions

Used in the ASE root, socket, connections, connection, or connection messages expressions to specify
    a auth:ConnectionMessageExpression. The connection messages directly or transitively reachable from all target nodes 
    become focus nodes of the connection message expression.
Used in an Authorization to define a set of [auth:Operation]s for which the [won:Node] provides authorization information in case of a negative authorization decision.

Sockets may define auth:Authorizaitons for the atoms they are added to and for the target atoms of
        connections that are made via the socket. These Authorizations are added to the atom's `#socket-acl` graph. In order
         to be able to remove the authorizations again when a socket is removed from the atom, the authorization links
         to the socket using auth:requestedBy.

auth:issuer is used to link indicate who did, was asked to, or is required as the issuer of a token.
    Note that it is not required that the issuer is identical with the signer of a token. Unless the property `auth:nodeSigned true` 
    is used, a token requested from an atom is signed by the WoN node on behalf of the atom. A token signed using
    the atom's private key can only be generated by the owner of the atom and thus involves a much more complex process
    to create.
The activeMQ topic to subscribe to to be informed when an atom is modified.
Indicates that a remote atom or remote connection supports the specified socket (=behavior) or specifies the remote socket to connect with.

comment.undefined: links a derived data graph to the connection state in which it was derived.

comment.en: The number of connections in the container that are in state CLOSED.
The number of connections in the container that are in state REQUEST_RECEIVED.
Specifies the prefix an atom must have on the node this specification applies to. This specification allows clients to generate new valid new Atom URIs.
Links a Connection to the Atom it belongs to (the source of this Connection)

comment.undefined: The Node's atoms, in a LDP-pageable container.

comment.en: The activeMQ queue to be used by matchers to send messages to the node.
The activeMQ topic to subscribe to to be informed when an atom is deactivated.

Used in the ASE root, socket or connections expressions to specify a auth:ConnectionExpression. The connections directly or transitively reachable from all target nodes become focus nodes of the connection expression.
Filters focus nodes of the socket expression by socket IRI (not to be confused with auth:socketType, which filters by IRI of the socket definition).
The activeMQ queue to be used by owners to send messages to the node.
Scope of an actual token, of a token to be granted, or required scope of a token to be accepted.
Used in a [auth:Authorization] to define constraints for [auth:AuthToken]s that if fulfilled, make their bearer a grantee.
The number of connections in the container that are in state SUGGESTED.

Used in ASEs to enumerate operations granted for the ASE's position in the atom's tree structure.
        When checking for granted operations, operations are inherited by nested ASEs. An ASE can reject inheriting
        the granted operations using `auth:inherit false`.
links a Connection to its remote Atom. The remote Atom is the one holding the  targetConnection.
Object properties of ASEs that have ASEs as their object.
Object properties of ASEs that do not have ASEs as their object.

Used in the ASE root to specify a auth:AtomMessagesExpression. The atom message containers reachable from all target nodes
    become focus nodes of the atom messages expression.
Links the socket to its definition. A socket must have exactly one definition.
Filters focus nodes of the graph expression by graph IRI.
Specifies the prefix a connection must have on the node this specification applies to.
The activeMQ topic to subscribe to to be informed when an atom is created.
Object properties of ASEs that do not have ASEs as their object.

Used in the ASE root, socket, connections, or connection expressions to specify
    a auth:ConnectionMessagesExpression. The connection containers directly or transitively reachable from all target nodes 
    become focus nodes of the connection messages expression.
Indicates the state in which the Connection object is.

Allows an auth:MessageOperationExpression to specify msg:MessageTypes that the grantee of the operation may
     send __to__ the atom, at the operation's position in the atom's tree structure. The message types are either
     listed as objects of auth:messageTo or defined transitively. In the latter case, the object of auth:messageTo
     is an auth:MessageTypeSet, which in turn lists message types.

Used in the ASE root or atom messages expressions to specify a auth:AtomMessageExpression. The atom
     messages directly or transitively reachable from all target nodes become focus nodes of the atom message expression.
Object properties that can be used to filter the focus nodes of ASE expressions.

Used in the ASE root or socket expressions to specify a auth:ConnectionsExpression. The connection containers directly or transitively reachable from all target nodes become focus nodes of the connections expression.
The activeMQ queue to be used by other nodes to send messages to the node.
The activeMQ topic to subscribe to to be informed when an atom is deleted.
Defines the Atom object's state.
Used in the ASE root to specify a auth:SocketExpression. All sockets of the atom become focus nodes of the socket expression.
Links an Atom to an RDF graph holding some of its RDF content.
Authorization that a socket requests the target atoms of its connections to add to their `#socket-acl` graphs upon establishing a connection.
Defines a property to be 'derived' when the connection is established. The property will be used to derive a triple '[sourceAtom] [property] [targetAtom]'.
Links a Connection object to its remote counterpart.
The activeMQ topic to subscribe to to be informed when an atom is activated.

If `true` or missing in an [auth:TokenSpecification], tokens are issued on behalf of [won:Atom]s by the [won:Node], and signed with the node's key. If `false`, tokens issued by an atom have to be signed using the atom's key. The latter is a much more complex process as the atom's key is only known to the owner applications controlling that atom; such tokens cannot be produced by the WoN node alone. If used in an [auth:TokenShape]the property instructs the token verification algorithm on which key to verify the signature against. By default, i.e., if this property is not used, tokens are assumed to be signed by the WoN node.
Specification of URI prefixes used by this WoN node.
Indicates the state in which the Connection was before the current one.
Links an Atom or Connection to their WoN node.

Used in an Authorization to define the set of grantees. Linking to an ASE root means that the targets
        of auth:TargetAtomExpressions are grantees. Linking to an atom expression means that the targets of
        the atom expression are grantees. Linking to a granteeWildcard means any client is a grantee.
The date/time the token expires, according to the signer's clock.
The relative or absolute reference to an atom.
The decision (access granted or denied) made by evaluating the ACL.
Indicates the socket to connect to by default.
The number of connections in the container that are in state CONNECTED.
A TokenOperationExpression links to the specification of the requested token via auth:requestToken.
The subject of an actual token - the atom that requested it.

Specifies the prefix a message must have on the node to which this specification applies. This specification allows clients to convert between a message URI (prefix 'wm:/') and a dereferencable https URI.
Identifies another SocketDefinition that is compatible with this one. Connections with other kinds of sockets will not be allowed unless they are explicitly annotated.
Filters focus nodes of the graph expression by graph type.
Links the Connection object to a container containing connection events (messages).
